did.abstract: This collection contains college catalogs from Central Washington University and its predecessors from 1892 to the present.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Office of the Registrar at Washington State Normal School was established in 1917. Prior to that date the office served under the principal of the school as secretary and recorder.

scopecontent.p: Along with general course catalogs for Central Washington University (and its predecessors), this collection also includes summer catalogs, film catalogs, faculty publication lists, and early reports from the Washington States Normal School's Board of Trustees.

odd.p: Central Washington University began as the Washington State Normal School in 1891. In 1937, the school was rechristened the Central Washington College of Education. In 1961, the school became Central Washington State College and, finally, in 1977, Central Washington University.

arrangement.p: Divided into undergraduate and graduate catalogs and bulletins, then arranged chronologically

accessrestrict.p: Open to the public for educational research
